HEADWORD: Sinking
<hw>Sink"ing</hw>, <def><pos>a. & n.</pos> from <er>Sink</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Sinking fund</b></col>. <cd>See under <er>Fund</er>.</cd>
-- <col><b>Sinking head</b></col> <fld>(Founding)</fld>, <cd>a riser
from which the mold is fed as the casting shrinks. See <er>Riser</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>, 4.</cd> -- <col><b>Sinking pump</b></col>, <cd>a pump
which can be lowered in a well or a mine shaft as the level of the water
sinks.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sinless</ent>⟦br⟧
